About data set¶

A cardiac tumor is an abnormal growth of tissue in the heart classified as either cancerous (malignant) or non-cancerous (benign).

information about columns¶

1.sex-¶

0 represents female whereas 1 represents male

2.trestbps(Resting blood pressure )-¶

High blood pressure = 140 mmHg or above

3.chol(Serum cholestoral)-¶

Higher than 200 mg/dL is concerned

4.fbs(Fasting blood sugar)-¶

0 represents < 120 mg/dL whereas 1 represents > 120 mg/dL Higher than 126 mg/dL points to diabetes

5.thalach-¶

Maximum heart rate achieved (bpm)

6.exang(Exercise induced angina)¶

0:Negative 1: Positive

7.oldpeak-¶

ST depression induced by exercise relative to rest

8.ca-¶

Number of major vessels (0-3) colored by fluoroscopy There is a clot if the blood vessel is not colored

9.target( Heart Disease)¶

0 :Benign 1 :Malignant
